main event: On March 9, 1959, an unidentified flying object was observed over Duluth, Minnesota, described by multiple witnesses, including pilots.
interesting points: The object was reported to move rapidly and change direction abruptly., The object was described as circular in shape, with a bright white light., Witnesses included military personnel who were trained observers., The sightings included both visual observations and radar tracking., The sightings occurred on multiple dates with consistent descriptions.
